Project Summary

This project demonstrates a full deployment of Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS) in a virtualized lab environment, including:

* Installing Windows Server
* Configuring static IP addressing
* Promoting server to Domain Controller
* Configuring DNS
* Setting up DHCP
* Creating Organizational Units (OUs)
* User and Group creation
* Group Policies (GPO)
* Login scripts
* Joining Windows clients
* Backup & Restore
* Hyper-V/VirtualBox networking
* AD DS health checks
* AD DS + Azure Hybrid preparation

This documentation is written for recruiters, technical reviewers, and hiring managers.



